<Group labelreference="L41" drawlabel="true">
<Input><Text-field style="Title" layout="Title">SSH package: documentation</Text-field><Text-field style="Normal" layout="Normal"><Font style="Help Bold">Description</Font>: SSH package provides SSH network protocol support via <Hyperlink linktarget="http://www.chiark.greenend.org.uk/~sgtatham/putty/" hyperlink="true"><Font underline="true" style="Normal">PuTTY</Font></Hyperlink> or similar client.</Text-field><Text-field style="Normal" layout="Normal"></Text-field><Text-field style="Normal" layout="Normal"><Font style="Help Bold">Installation</Font>: you can install SSH module as a package or read SSH.ini file at the beginning of your worksheet. When the package is being loaded, user configuration is read from <Font style="Code">cat(UserConfigurationFolder,&quot;SSH_Setup.ini&quot;)</Font> file.</Text-field><Text-field style="Normal" layout="Normal"></Text-field><Text-field style="Normal" layout="Normal"><Font style="Help Bold">Requirements</Font>: tested for Windows,<Hyperlink linktarget="http://www.chiark.greenend.org.uk/~sgtatham/putty/" hyperlink="true"></Hyperlink> PuTTY-like SSH client, md5 checksum program (e.g. <Hyperlink linktarget="http://support.microsoft.com/kb/841290" hyperlink="true"><Font underline="true" style="Normal">FCIV</Font></Hyperlink>), untar/ungz utilities (e.g. 7za). For convenience put all executables into one folder included in PATH environment variable.</Text-field><Text-field style="Normal" layout="Normal"></Text-field><Text-field style="Normal" layout="Normal"><Font style="Help Bold">List of commands</Font> (for their usage see the examples below, SSH.ini, and PuTTY documentation):</Text-field><Text-field style="Normal" layout="Normal"></Text-field><Text-field style="Normal" layout="Normal"><Font style="Code">Setup -</Font> configure the package and the connection (provide host and ppk-file at least), see SSH_Setup.ini</Text-field><Text-field style="Normal" layout="Normal"></Text-field><Text-field style="Normal" layout="Normal"><Font style="Code">opentunnel -</Font> open a tunnel using port forwarding</Text-field><Text-field style="Normal" layout="Normal"></Text-field><Text-field style="Normal" layout="Normal"><Font style="Code">login  -</Font> run interactive SSH client using <Font style="Help Fixed">putty</Font> program (interactive SSH-client)</Text-field><Text-field style="Normal" layout="Normal"><Font style="Code">run    -</Font> run a command on a remote machine using <Font style="Help Fixed">plink</Font> program (command SSH-client)</Text-field><Text-field style="Normal" layout="Normal"><Font style="Code">runftp -</Font> run a command using <Font style="Help Fixed">psftp</Font> program (ftp SSH-client)</Text-field><Text-field style="Normal" layout="Normal"></Text-field><Text-field style="Normal" layout="Normal"><Font style="Code">pwd -</Font> return active remote directory</Text-field><Text-field style="Normal" layout="Normal"><Font style="Code">dir -</Font> list the remote directory</Text-field><Text-field style="Normal" layout="Normal"><Font style="Code">put -</Font> upload files</Text-field><Text-field style="Normal" layout="Normal"><Font style="Code">get -</Font> download files</Text-field><Text-field style="Normal" layout="Normal"><Font style="Code">sget -</Font> download files and folders securely</Text-field><Text-field style="Normal" layout="Normal"><Font style="Code">FileExists -</Font> check if the remote file exists</Text-field><Text-field style="Normal" layout="Normal"><Font style="Code">FileStatus -</Font> check file status: 0 - does not exist, 1 - directory, 2 - executable, 3 - other</Text-field><Text-field style="Normal" layout="Normal"></Text-field><Text-field style="Normal" layout="Normal"><Font style="Code">qsub -</Font> submit job</Text-field><Text-field style="Normal" layout="Normal"><Font style="Code">qdel -</Font> delete job</Text-field><Text-field style="Normal" layout="Normal"><Font style="Code">qstat -</Font> run qstat command on a remote machine</Text-field><Text-field style="Normal" layout="Normal"><Font style="Code">pbsnodes -</Font> print information on nodes managed by <Hyperlink linktarget="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Portable_Batch_System" hyperlink="true"><Font underline="true" style="Normal">PBS</Font></Hyperlink> such as <Hyperlink linktarget="http://www.adaptivecomputing.com/resources/docs/torque/2-5-9/index.php" hyperlink="true"><Font underline="true" style="Normal">TORQUE</Font></Hyperlink></Text-field><Text-field style="Normal" layout="Normal"><Font style="Code">pbsreports -</Font> print list of PBS report files</Text-field><Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal"></Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
